24/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The defence ministry launched two days of talks Monday (24 May) with its US counterpart, focusing on security and co-operation.
Macedonia's role in global anti-terrorism activities will be discussed, as well as military reforms, border management and weapons upgrades.
Skopje also will seal a bilateral agreement on preventing the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.
Also Monday, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski is in Rome, where officials reiterated their support for Macedonia's integration into Euro-Atlantic structures.
Crvenkovski is there to mark Cyrillic Literacy Day.
(MIA - 24/05/04)
